pageTitle: CDC - Obesity FOA - Counties with Adult Obesity Prevalence Over 40%
TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {10463=The list of counties with an adult obesity prevalence of over 40% is based on obesity estimates generated with the use of small-area statistical modelling. To create the estimates, a multilevel logistic regression model with both state-and nested country-level random effects for obesity prevalence was developed using data from the 2012 Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System. Post-stratification with the US Census 2010 counts of census-block populations was applied to the models to generate census-block level estimates which were then aggregated to a county level. A detailed description of the methodology is described in Zhang et al.1}
